{"by":"iwd","id":47777773,"kids":[47778456],"parent":47740840,"text":"I just got to see a different species of kleptoplastic sea slugs in the wild last month, on a kayak tour of the mangroves around Key West. Our guide scooped some lettuce sea slugs up in a plastic container (and then returned them safely).  They were bigger, about 3 inches long, with a wavy&#x2F;frilly green border. It made my biologist heart very happy!","time":1776253546,"type":"comment"}